    'body' => '>> I\'m still a bit captivated over Joseph Dietrich\'s TU, and would
>> like to set out some ideas for anyone who is also a bit captivated.
>
>What is this? Does it have a link to his page or is this some kind of
>prited material?


No, actually it\'s just a developing idea that me and Robert have discussed.
I\'m trying to develop my next Traveller game, and I\'ve asked a couple of
questions to the list (the fuel-less jump drive thread having garnered the
most responses). Roberts been very helpful to me in generating ideas on the
setting at large.

In brief, it\'s space opera/science fantasy pure and simple, with a huge
dose of Fading Suns-style neogothicisim, using the Imperium as a backdrop.
Originally it was going to be set in the Rebellion era, but it\'s starting
to develop into a post-rebellion, post-hard times setting.

As part of the flavor, I wanted jump drives that didn\'t use huge amounts of
jump fuel. I also am going to have a lot of Ancient relics laying about,
including some huge jump gates that allow transit from certain strategic
sytems to others.

Other elements include a lot of ignorance of technology, a religious
revival in the form of a Universal Church, psionics,
things-man-was-not-meant-to-know, secret societies, and other phenomena
strange and mysterious.

I was thinking about calling the setting _Dark Imperium_ or some such thing.

The only stuff I have up on a webpage that\'s Traveller-related are some
things that I did for my *last* game, which was also space opera, but with
a Star Wars flavor (and using the SW-RPG rules). Alas, it was all hand
