Rob\'s DSDS "Dirty Ship Design System"


Rob\'s Base Assumptions for DSDS:

   1. No calculator necessary!
   2. If it\'s less than one order of magnitude off, it\'s ok.
   3. Unless otherwise stated or absurd, ignore fractions.
   4. This is for spaceships only.
   5. This is most useful for prototyping.
   6. This is not useful for detailed design.
   7. This may look similar to CT\'s system...


System     Volume            Cost      Power       Crew
- ----  ----            ---- ---- ----
Hull       hull size         0           0         0
J-drive    hull/100 per pc   MCr4/dton   0         1 per 10 dtons
M-drive    hull/100 per G    MCr3/dton  10 MW/dton 1 per 20 dtons
Turrets    3 dtons                                 1 gunner per turret
 Laser     "                 MCr1       50 MW
 Missile * "                 MCr0.1      0
 Sand    * "                 MCr0.2      0
Bridge     10 + hull/50      KCr5/dton   0         1 per 20 dtons (round up)
Power      1 dton per 25 MW  MCr3/dton   0         1 per 10 dtons
Fuel     **
Refinery   1dt=10dt per hr   MCr10/dton  0         1 per 10 dtons
Berths                       MCr0.1/dton 0
  Pass     4 dton per pass   "                     1 steward per 10 pass.
  Crew     2 dton per crew+1 "                     1 command per 10 crew
  Low      1 dton per        "                     1 medic per 10 low berths


*Ammo      max 15 per appropriate turret
 Missile   MCr0.1 and up
 Sand      MCr0.01

** Fuel Volume: 10% hull volume per jump-parsec
              + 1 dton per 10 MW power (round down)



