    'body' => '>Hi all.  The recent discussion of IBIS and IRIS got me thinking:  What are
>the intelligence services and secret societies in the TU?  I\'ve invented a
>few of my own, but I don\'t remember seeing many in the sourcebooks.  In
>fact, this seems a little suspicious to me.  Has there been some sort of
>cover up?  Perhaps the answer lies in <CENSORED> <CENSORED> <CENSORED>
><CENSORED> <CENSORED>

IMTU, the Scout Service has an ultra-covert intelligence service called
The Rangers, who use mundane Scout activities as their cover. As far as
most people are concerned, they\'re just scouts. A few might learn that
they\'re part of the IISS\' Intelligence Branch. But a very select few 
know the truth: they\'re part of a group that is secret enough that even
most IISS Intelligence Branch members don\'t know it exists.

The reason it exists IMTU is that the player characters are members of
this elite service. Their being Scouts gives them cover to travel around
the sector without being particularly noticed; being Intelligence agents
gives them their adventures...

Other agencies that probably exist IMTU include IRIS and ISIS and IBIS
and the other usual groups. I have an adventure planned where the PCs
will have to deal with the operatives of one of these services who are
working at cross-purposes with what the PCs are trying to do, each group
not wanting to reveal who they really are to the other... :)

