but....

What you\'re saying is you have two factors, the levels of Law and of
Corruption.  Put one on one axis and the other on the other...


 High | B                      C
      |
      |
 Law  |
      |
      |
      |
      |
      |  A                     D
  Low |______________________________
      Low                         High
                  Corruption

  A = Few laws or law officers, but the police/sherrif/judges are
      generally an honest and honorable.  I many cases, the judges
      and police work with the "spirit of the law" rather than
      depending on the letter.  An attempted bribe would be
      considered insulting and dealt with harshly.  The "honest
      west" of fiction.
      
  B = There are laws and regulations for almost everything, and they
      are enforced strictly.  Bribes attempts are dealt with harshly
      by the almost uniformly honest legal system.  This could be
      anything from a world like "Repent Hariquin, Said the Tick
      Tock Man", to an idealized totalitarian state.
      
  C = Again, laws and regulations for almost everthing, but the
      police and courts are more than willing to ignore
      *anything*...for a price.  In fact if you don\'t attempt to
      bribe an offical you are probably going to be dealt with very
      harshly.  You better hope you don\'t have enemies that can
      afford to outspend you or you will have the authorities out to
      get you, too.  The extreme would be like the movie "Brazil" or
      maybe "Max Headroom"...or a more realistic totalitarian state.
      
  D = There are few laws or regulations on the books, but the
      "authorities" will shake you down for bribes and payoffs on
      trumpped up charges anyway.  They are probably especially
      rough on outsiders and travellers.  You have to worry about
      these thugs staying bought, too.  Something like a Clint
      Eastwood western, certain real third world countries. or
      (mostly fictional) backwater county govenments in the rural
      American south.
      
Is there something like this in WBH?

