    'subj' => 'Re: Cons On Ice Scenario Idea',
    'from' => 'Richard Hough corvus@telus.net',
    'body' => '>Ya know, I\'ve been thinking about (actually Larry Niven did it first, and it
>was the thread about his books combined with this one that got me thinking
>about it!) Given the way J drive works, and the thruster limitations given
>in T4, how would you catch an STL ship?

Assuming thrust plates only work in a 100 diameter radius of a 
gravity well you can extend their range by accelerating near a large 
object, like a gas giant or star, then jump to where you estimate 
your target will be in a week.

If even this wasn\'t enough space to accelerate you\'d have to use 
multiple jumps, probably with drop tanks so you can still jump back 
into thrust plate range after your rendezvous.

I can imagine that for objects with a really high normal-space speed 
(near-c rocks?) you would use several jumps with several drop tanks. 
Boost the tanks to higher and higher speeds, timing them to intercept 
the expected ship arrival time and speed. Each time the ship pops out 
of jump it drops the spent tanks and docks with the boosted tanks, 
all while accelerating, and jumps again to the next drop tank 
interception point.
- --
Richard Hough
rdhough@telus.net
