    'body' => 'Ok...made it!!!! I was able to get a few of the Keith Supplements into the
mail today before the post-office closed at noon. Worked the remainer of
the day and have several more ready to send out on monday. 

Several have written and asked \'how\' I am sending them out - I am posting
them in the order that I received payment - have all those placed in August
and September of 1998 are mailed/ready to mail, and I will be working on
those placed in October of 1998 tomorrow.

Several have also written and asked if I have any sets left. The answer is
yes - around 30. Ordering information is still available on the website,
which I will update once I have a spare moment. Any new orders placed
before Dec.8th will still include free copies of the Imperial Calendar and
the Reavers\' Deep Sector Sourcebook.

As I memtioned in my post earlier this week, I will be printing/mailing out
sets up until Dec. 8th, at which time I am going on a three-week trip. I
will resume printing/mailing any remaining orders when I return home the
4th of Janurary.

Before I forget - due to real-life time-contraints, I scrapped plans to
print up and include as \'freebies\' the MegaTraveller I & II Cluebooks and
the manuals for Space I & II. If anyone who ordered a set was seriously
looking forward to these, please send me an email after the new year and I
will see about getting you a copy. Even though the sets are lacking the
intended freebies mentioned above, I hope the quality of the Imperial
Calendar, and especially the Reavers\' Deep Sourcebook will make up for it.

Speaking of the Reavers\' Deep Sourcebook, I would like to thank all those
who helped contribute both their time and effort to it - in particular
Jimmy Simpson and Hans Ranke.

Ok...I think that about covers it. I hope you folks enjoy the Supplements.
This whole experience has been one of learning for me, and I want to
appoligise one last time for the delay in getting them out. If you spot any
serious errors/typos, please send me an email.

Cordially,
Paul Sanders
timmon@primenet.com
