    'body' => 'GypsyComet wrote:
>>>>>>>>>>>
 Advancement in the nobility of the Consulate has more to do with
the desire to lead and the responsibility to do so. At every level
the nobles are a democracy amongst themselves, regardless of how
they handle the Proles that are their responsibility.<snip>
 The closest I\'ve come to describing this is "Democratic Meritocracy."
>>>>>>>>>>>
There are strict limits to one\'s social standing if one does not have
psionic powers, and one\'s social standing can increase based on
successful use of these psionic powers - at least, they can during 
the Zhodani character generation procedure, with involvement in
the psionic olympics. I agree that posession of and power level of
psionic powers is not the only facet of Zhodani social standing, it
is the facet that is most different from that of the Third Imperium.

Can you call the ruling oligarchy Charismatic if they use mind control
to gain for themselves the support of the governed?  ;-)

One thing I\'ve wondered about the Zhodani Mind-Rapers vs Zhodani
Super-Psychologists: if the first thing you learn about something
very complicated is how to make it behave in a very simple fashion
that suits your needs, how good will you actually get at understanding
the very complex parts of it?

Let\'s say that Zhodani psionic adepts learn to read and alter minds.
Is it a necessity that they learn the entire workings of the human
brain to impose a desired mental state upon it? Can a dissatisfied
prole be turned into a happy prole by just applying Mental State #37
(Happy, Loyal Prole) on top of whatever real problems that prole had?
Perhaps the prole will still have those problems, but be unable to
express them or act upon them...or even let anyone know that they
still exist.

If this technique makes a troublemaker stop being a troublemaker,
will the adepts take the time and effort needed to get a better
understanding of the human mind? I know they can just open up
their telepathy and take a look - but I can look at a cell through
a microscope, that doesn\'t mean I understand cellular metabolism.

The Zhodani technique could be something as simple as laying in
a few commands - "Do Not Question The Social Order." 
"Fulfill Your Assigned Tasks Quickly And Efficiently."
"Present A Happy And Contented Attitude To Everyone You Meet."
Now the person\'s brain warps here and there to accomodate these
iron, unchangeable commands, like a rain forest might warp to 
accomodate a four-lane expressway. The expressway builder didn\'t
need to know much at all about the rain forest, and didn\'t care - as
long as he could cut down or pave over anything in his way. Simple
wins over complex by making it simple.

Once a simple, reliable technique is developed for keeping the proles
in line, will the Zhodani Tvarcheedle spend their resources working on
a more complex technique that\'s nicer to the proles\' brains, or will they
instead work on making the simple (though brutal) technique more
effective and more efficient?

Walt Smith
