information that was posted a few digests back, are :-
i. Point defence device - intercept incoming nukes.
ii. \'Damper box\' - items within a damping field have more (or less)
stable nuclei. E.g. theatre of ops/city (installation)/vehicle
protection/stabilising californium munitions.

So a disintegrator induces instability in the target\'s atoms, which is
opposed by the damper in \'box\' mode.
(?alters strong or electroweak force/suppresses electron or proton
charge/perturbs local constants e.g. changes gravitational and
electromag interactions from inverse square to some other power, or
varies Planck constant/free space permittivity/G?)

