The walls of a fuel tank actually consists of two layers: a rigid outer
layer and a flexible, collapsible inside layer. As the fuel is expended,
the inner layer begins to collapse, leaving vacuum between it and the 
outside layer. When the tank gets filled, the inner layer expands again
to fill the inside...

