    'body' => 'Fellow Travellers,

I have a dream... I have a dream of a program, a very nifty and useful
program that I would write -- if only I had any programming skills.  Sadly,
I have none, so I must ask for the assistance of the programmers on the
list...

On my Mac, I have an After Dark screensaver module called "Planetmaker" --
a very nifty fractal planet map generator.  I had plans to use it to
quickly generate realistic world maps for MTU.

Planetmaker\'s great, but unfortunately the resulting maps are rectangular
Mercator projections.  But a true Traveller map should of course be
icosahedral (i.e. Fuller dymaxion projections), I can\'t help wishing there
was some way to generate Planetmaker-style fractal maps in icosahedral
format.  Now wouldn\'t that be a cool program?

