overlaid hex grids (I don\'t find \'em entirely useful, myself), preferably
in postscript.

Of course, as a Mac addict, I would prefer to see Mac software, or
MRJ-compatible Java.

The ability to generate maps based on UWPs (or Hydrographic percentages at
least) would be a bonus, but not entirely necessary.   One could always
generate a bunch of maps and match them up with appropriate worlds.

Is there any chance some devoted TML programmer might be able to take on
such a project?  Or (dare I hope?) has some kind soul already done it?

Or am I just dreaming in holographic Technicolor?

