Whether Her Australian Magesty reigns or not is actually not an issue in terms
of Commonwealth membership. You can be a millitary dictator and stil have a seat
at CHOGM (Commomwealth Heads of Government Meeting). It was brought up in the
debate, but since South Africa, Malaysia, Singapore and others do not have QEII
as head of state, it is a bit rich.I personally was of two minds on the
republic, as I was loath to loose all the cool imperial monikers and pagents.

