    'from' => 'Leonard Erickson',
    'body' => 'In mail you write:

> Well, the setting is non cannon, so the 30,000 years is no problem.
> But I try to avoid over using the Ancients so they don\'t get boring
> to the players.

One of Traveller\'s shortcomings is that while it borrowed the idea of
"Forerunners" from Norton and others, they made them a *single*
civilization. Norton handles the concept the best with the term being
rather generic and applying to *any* interstellar capable civilization
that was gone before any of the currently exist ones arrived on the
scene. This gives you civilizations running from ones that vanished
only a little before her Zacathans hit the scene (around 10k years
back) to ones that vanished hundreds of thousands of years ago. 

So you can\'t get bored, because you\'re dealing with cultures that were
widely seperated in time, space, or both. And that were very
*different* from each other.

- -- 
