Take the Tavershedzle (sp?)... they don\'t look so much for the unhappy, as
those who are leaning towards ciminality. There is a reference to "unhapy"
zhodani... and being unhappy is NOT grounds for reducation, unless such
unhappiness is leading one to criminality. The big difference socially is
that the mental processes leading to ciminal beahviour are themselves the
crime. The term is translated erroneously to "Thought Police", the text
defines it as "Guardians of Our Morality", and defines the role in that
light. They find those who are a-moral or immoral, by zhodani standards,
and (forcibly, if needed) help them build a moral code in line with
standard Zhodani ethical standards. Note also that even nobles are subject
to re-education, by the standard techniques.

Also, the definitions of Crimes in the Consulate are very different: Crimes
of neglect, Crimes of Passion, and Crimes of Insanity. The former are
usually fines, lest you commmit them repeatedly or REQUEST reeducation on
them. Crimes of Passion are seen as temporary breaks of self-control due to
unusual stress, and are punished with reparitions and counselling,
sometimes reeducation into a new situation (Read job & location) where such
stresses are less likely. Crimes of insanity are all other crimes... the
thought processes which result in the criminal intent are edited out, and
new methods found to deal with such stresses....

See "Lacy and His Friends", IICR by M Lackey, for an example of rediredtion
of abberant impulses in a non-psionic but very nearly Zhodani society...
Lacy must masturbate, when he gets his abberant behavioural impulse (He was
a rapist); Lacy\'s rewiring includes not being able to get an errection with
a female nearby, and IIRC, even outside the appropriate locations.

The material in Adv 0 also jives with the "Benevolent Tavrshedzle" mode...
but is vague enough not to conflict with either mode.

