the marines ready to drop, as well as sending a team of nobles, with
huscarles, to "Visit the Local Noble", and defend the starport. Also, the
local "Imperial Forces" (IE, locally raised troops subject to imperial
activation) would be activated and shipped elsewhere for the duration. And
a team of diplomats would remind the government that withdrawl means an
absolute interdict.

If they DO withdraw peacefully, they merely get interdicted... The navy and
marines evacuate all who wish to leave, and take over the starports. Anyone
leaving gets informed that the trip out is one way. All extraplanetary
(Inlcuding in-system) trade gets supressed. The military personell shipped
elsewhere are informed they may not return home. The navy shoots down
blockade runners. Marine drops assault anybody who DOES make it through, as
soon as they are found. And the local noble is "Protected" by his
Huscarles, and imperial forces, to await the re-entry petition.

If they Withdraw by force, they lose all industrial bases, all who take up
arms are barred from imperial citizenship, but still considered subjects.
The marines impose martial law. The navy wipes out all satellite systems.
The iron fist cranks down on EVERYONE on-world... those wishing to flee had
better be able to prove off-world connections (or citizenship); in which
case they will be excorted off from the starports, much like above. And a
full interdict for the duration of the "insurrection", much as above.

In either case, the local noble gets protected. He\'s the escape route for
the government... he\'s the one they petition to to get off planet. And, for
the duration, the Navy keeps his hold well stocked, and recieving
goodies... and smugglers get the 4mm Gauss to the back... Tours (of
disarmed locals) are often set up, just to remind everyone how much better
it was. Anyone entering the estate gets searched and disarmed, with a no
punishment, and no return of contraband, policy. Come and see how the
Imperials live... Price: lose any weapons you might be carrying, and exit
with only clothes...

