>themselves but change others minds  (prole) to side with them.

Shodani have 3 "Castes", the upper and lower being Nobles and Proles, both
of which have multiple social strata. The third caste, the intendants, is a
middle caste, composed of born intendants and those prole children adopted
into noble families due to high psionic potential. This third caste, can,
if enough merit is shown, be promoted to the nobility. Prole children with
high psionic potential become proles. By inference, one can assume
non-heirs of the nobility might also revert to intendant status.

The Nobility are policed by themselves, and also by the Tavershedzle. Note
that not all psionicists can shield; telepaths can, but non-telepaths
cannot. The Tavershedzle tend to draw from the intendant caste. The
Tavrshedzle are almost entirely telepaths of some level. All intendants and
nobles are psionically trained. Promotions appear to be based upon Job
Performance Merit, rather than Psionic merit. The worst case would be a
block of Tavrshedzle rebelling, but in general, the result would be much
like any "Noble Revolt" anywhere else... the other nobles would put it down
with a fury. Also note that zhodani do know about artificial psionic
shielding, and much better than imperial techs do at same tech level; they
use it  for switches by TL 12! so they could quite easily send in forces
with shields once they suspect a revolt. Additionally, should a higher
noble arrive and publicly announce the "relief due to needing treatment" of
a rebellious noble, the populace would likely believe it, and do everything
possible to see to it he was cured.

Also note that, despite propaganda, Psionics play little in the day to day
life of Proles. Proles, even if not happy, know that they can become happy
upon request. They have no stigma against mental illness, a much better
understanding of the pathology, and how to treat (if not cure) most mental
illnesses; also, they have a much more liberal definition of a mental
illness than most of us on the list.

BTW, the example on page 14 of AM4-Zhodani notes the following (post
pick-up by the TP):
	"A few days later, the Prole returns home, much happier. His new
job is exactly what he needs and wants; a perfect outlet for his ambitions.
His successful neighbor, he now knows, leads a shallow life without the
enjoyment and fulfilment that it should have. The world itself seems
brighter and clearer."
	This pattern seems to indicate a number of things happened during
his stay with the reeducators:
1)	placed into a job better suited to his temperment and abilities (if
not existing skills)
2)	purged of jealousy via "programming"
3)	probable surgical and/or chemical alteration of any underlying
depression or anxiety disorders,
4)	the Prole is reassured that SOCIETY CARES enough to want to see him
well.

also mentioned on p14 is that the "... result is excellent diagnosis and
careful treatment in reeducation centers. When treatment is complete, the
individual rejoins society without any stigma or blot on his record..."

>Also as far as art work goes I think the Zhodani would have a cool
>since of visional/mental art. I can see them doing direct imput. Or
>you can do what I did for a Mage (tm) with an artist who had mind
>read/control.  His art respondant to the viwer.  So lets say its a sea
>painting and the viwer thought of a stormy sea.  The art would
>change to a stormy sea.  Though in this case the artist would have
>to be there.
>
Not particularly likely... there is no evidence of "sustained phenomena" in
the rules norr in canon, nor is there any evidence of direct psionically
active hardware (with the possible exception of Virus, but that\'s for
another day/flame-war). Mage assumes you change the collective reality;
Psionics in traveller are merely "as yet unproven quantum-physics
macro-effects"[1]. At best, a noble or intendant might share his conception
of the finished sculpture to Prole Artisans, and have them do the labor...

[1] well, not exactly "as yet unknown". A recent study (replicated at least
once) showed that human desire for a particular direction of result from a
computerized random number generator can in fact skew the results. on a
1-200 scale, it swung the results by 10 points in the desired direction
(mean went from 100 to 110 when high was desired, from 100 to 90 when low
was desired). Line of sight was not required. Range was not tested
thoroughly, but exceeded 250m. It is the first study to have been
replicated that showed discernable psionic phenomena. Even the Amazing
Randi has yet to be willing to address the study, in whole or in part,
publically. Have seen the study cited in 4 different shows, including
Discover Magazine (the TV Programme).

