FW: (Fwd) FW: IN TIME FOR REMEMBRANCE......In time for Remembrance =
Day.....=20

=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=20
THE NIGHT BEFORE CHRISTMAS=20
\'TWAS THE NIGHT BEFORE CHRISTMAS,=20
HE LIVED ALL ALONE,=20
IN A ONE BEDROOM HOUSE=20
MADE OF PLASTER AND STONE.=20

I HAD COME DOWN THE CHIMNEY=20
WITH PRESENTS TO GIVE,=20
AND TO SEE JUST WHO=20
IN THIS HOME DID LIVE.=20

I LOOKED ALL ABOUT,=20
A STRANGE SIGHT I DID SEE,=20
NO TINSEL, NO PRESENTS,=20
NOT EVEN A TREE.=20

NO STOCKING BY MANTLE,=20
JUST BOOTS FILLED WITH SAND,=20
ON THE WALL HUNG PICTURES=20
OF FAR DISTANT LANDS.=20

WITH MEDALS AND BADGES,=20
AWARDS OF ALL KINDS,=20
A SOBER THOUGHT=20
CAME THROUGH MY MIND.=20

FOR THIS HOUSE WAS DIFFERENT,=20
IT WAS DARK AND DREARY,=20
I FOUND THE HOME OF A SOLDIER,=20
ONCE I COULD SEE CLEARLY.=20

THE SOLDIER LAY SLEEPING,=20
SILENT, ALONE,=20
CURLED UP ON THE FLOOR=20
IN THIS ONE BEDROOM HOME.=20

THE FACE WAS SO GENTLE,=20
THE ROOM IN SUCH DISORDER,=20
NOT AT ALL=20
HOW I PICTURED SOLDIER.=20

WAS THIS THE HERO OF WHOM I\'D JUST READ?=20
CURLED UP ON A PONCHO, THE FLOOR FOR A BED?=20
I REALIZED THE FAMILIES=20
THAT I SAW THIS NIGHT,=20
OWED THEIR LIVES TO THESE SOLDIERS=20
WHO WERE WILLING TO FIGHT.=20

SOON ROUND THE WORLD,=20
THE CHILDREN WOULD PLAY,=20
AND GROWNUPS WOULD CELEBRATE=20
A BRIGHT CHRISTMAS DAY.=20

THEY ALL ENJOYED FREEDOM=20
EACH MONTH OF THE YEAR,=20
BECAUSE OF THE SOLDIERS,=20
LIKE THE ONE LYING HERE.=20

I COULDN\'T HELP WONDER=20
HOW MANY LAY ALONE,=20
ON A COLD CHRISTMAS EVE=20
IN A LAND FAR FROM HOME.=20

THE VERY THOUGHT=20
BROUGHT A TEAR TO MY EYE,=20
I DROPPED TO MY KNEES=20
AND STARTED TO CRY=20

THE SOLDIER AWAKENED=20
AND I HEARD A ROUGH VOICE,=20
"SANTA DON\'T CRY,=20
THIS LIFE IS MY CHOICE;=20

I FIGHT FOR FREEDOM,=20
I DON\'T ASK FOR MORE,=20
MY LIFE IS MY GOD,=20
MY COUNTRY, MY CORPS."=20

THE SOLDIER ROLLED OVER=20
AND DRIFTED TO SLEEP,=20
I COULDN\'T CONTROL IT,=20
I CONTINUED TO WEEP.=20

I KEPT WATCH FOR HOURS,=20
SO SILENT AND STILL=20
AND WE BOTH SHIVERED=20
FROM THE COLD NIGHT\'S CHILL.=20

I DIDN\'T WANT TO LEAVE=20
ON THAT COLD, DARK,NIGHT,=20
THIS GUARDIAN OF HONOR=20
SO WILLING TO FIGHT.=20

THEN THE SOLDIER ROLLED OVER, WITH A VOICE SOFT AND PURE, WHISPERED, =
"CARRY=20
ON SANTA, IT\'S CHRISTMAS DAY, ALL IS SECURE." ONE LOOK AT MY WATCH, AND =
I=20
KNEW HE WAS RIGHT.=20
"MERRY CHRISTMAS MY FRIEND, AND TO ALL A GOOD NIGHT."=20
This poem was written by a Marine stationed in=20
Okinawa Japan.  The=20
following is his request. I think it is=20
reasonable.....=20

PLEASE. Would you do me the kind favor of sending this to as many people =
as=20
you can? Christmas will be coming soon and some credit is due to our=20
U.S.and Canadian service men and women for our being able to celebrate=20
these festivities.=20
Let\'s try in this small way to pay a tiny bit of what we owe. Make =
people=20
stop and think of our heroes, living and dead, who sacrificed themselves =

for us. Please, do your small part to plant this small seed.=20


