    'index' => 'ed712',
    'month' => '11',
    'topic' => 're: recovering disabled grav vehicles',
    'body' => 'I think we\'ll find recovery vehicles for Grav Tanks built at TL8, 7, or even
below.

Many worlds in the Imperium have low tech levels, but will see a need
to buy higher-tech defensive equipment, at steep prices. There\'s
really no point in building TL 6 tanks, if your most probable opponent
will be landing TL12+ grav vehicles from space...it would be better
for you to buy some TL 12+ grav vehicles, at least more than you 
expect a corsair, raider or star viking to bring with them. 

(Of course, this only applies if your world is unified and relatively stable.
If you\'re balkanized or have significant insurgents, build what you can
and buy what you can.)

You would build support equipment at the local tech level, if possible. 
A TL7 truck with a crane and a lowboy trailer could probably recover a 
disabled grav vehicle, as could a TL 7 heavy-lift helicopter or even a 
zeppelin. Such vehicles might have a problem keeping up with grav 
formations, but will cost a lot less to build and maintain and may be
easily convertable from what you\'re generally using locally for cargo 
transport.

The image of a cargo zeppelin recovering a disabled grav APC is 
somewhat appealing to me for some reason.

Reference the local support of the Allied war effort in the Burma-Indochina
theater of war during World War II. Airfields were created and maintained 
entirely through hand labor, as no bulldozers could be brought  to many 
sites. Some downed aircraft were recovered, at least for parts, by use of 
elephants or other beasts of burden.

Walt Smith
