    'body' => 'At 11:09 AM -0500 11/10/99, 
owner-traveller-digest@lists.imagiconline.com (Traveller-diges wrote:
>  >         Anyone remember the cheesy sci-fi about the humans on the Arc?
>
>Earthship Ark.  Had an actor that was later Chekov (SP?) didn\'t it?

The Starlost, an extremely low-budget Canadian sci-fi TV series which 
came out in 1973, after Star Trek. Walter Koenig was in several 
episodes.

I can understand why you thought it came out before Star Trek; the 
effects were so primitive it looks like something made by a 
high-school drama class.

This program was the result of some hard work by eastern Canadian 
sci-fi fans, who got Harlan Ellison to write the pilot and Douglas 
Trumbull to produce it. Unfortunately, the budget could not meet 
Ellison\'s vision for the series and he disavowed it. He even demanded 
they change his name in the credits to "Cordwainer Bird".

I remember reading an essay from someone involved with the series. 
The budget constraints and clueless management were so extreme it was 
funny. Ellison was in a huge argument with a "professional" 
(non-sci-fi) writer who thought a "backup computer" was something 
that made the spaceship fly in reverse.
