It is not mine. Yukio Mishima had that "Army" in modern-times Japan, 
and he did die by commiting ritual suicide (set the record for depth 
and width in the cuts, IIRC). They were not exactly pacifists as we 
westerners understand the concept, but there is where I took the idea 
from.

> > They were sort of a peaceful resistance against the 
> > growing corporate power. Their ritual, spectacular suicides as 
> > protest for specific corporate acts (like causing planetary wars to 
> > control mineral resources) received a disproportionate media coverage
> > and caused negative demand reactions among the consumers, eventually 
> > forcing the corporations to pay attention to the movement.
 
> What sort of methods for their ritual suicide did they use? The 
> old standby of some kind of bladed weapon or something more modern? 
> Or setting themselves on fire? Or something totally different?

To be honest, in the first adventure I was thinking quick and had 
some of them (asian descent) use the traditional methods 
(hara-kiri/seppuku), complete with a *robotic* assistant programmed 
by themselves as a credible commitment. Later, I portrayed them as 
using a variety of suicide methods related to the issue they were 
protesting for, and gaining in spectacularity to captivate the 
mass-media attention. The only requirement is that it must be the 
individual\'s will and personal action what causes death, overcoming 
the pain of the process, and not some natural force (there is a huge 
difference between an "actice" suicide as seppuku and a "passive" 
suicide as jumping from a building - the jump does not kill you, but 
the fall)

For example, when the Geoneecide started, most of the initial victims 
(IMTU) died when Margaret\'s fleet destroyed Geonee-full starships 
which were fleeing the ravaged Massilia. Marquis Tanzer (?), the 
leading force behind the Geoneecide, stated that because the 
Geonee\'s internals organs were so packed, it was difficult to 
capture them alive, which explained the number of deaths.

One "Mishiman" killed himself in presence of Margaret by  using two 
robotic arms which augmented the strength of his own arms to compress 
the lower part of his body, "packing his internal organs to Geonee 
density." Another one killed stole a naval shuttle and used a 
remote-controlled cargo loader to have it slowly crush himself - he 
was pushing a lever to that purpose and could have stopped any 
second, but didn\'t.

Oh, btw, the PCs thought the Mishimans were all crazy, but the events 
*did* catch their attention. Then I throwed a Geonee "Mishiman" in as 
NPC...

Carlos Alos-Ferrer
