    'from' => 'Glenn Goffin gmgoffin@yahoo.com',
    'body' => '>From: "The Roc" <roc@kewl.com.au>

>ObTrav:  Will the Imperium take by force any system
>that wishes to leave it\'s fold?  Are the systems that

>as independent, would still hold close ties
>to the Empire and not be subject to force of 
>compliancy?  Is there anything canon about such 
>worlds/systems?

I don\'t think canon addresses the issue, but I\'ve
always assumed that once you\'ve joined the Imperium,
you can\'t leave -- and once the Imperium decides it
wants you, all you can do is cut the best deal you
can.  

All of those oaths of fealty and pledges of allegiance
that the government signs when the world joins the
Imperium say "in perpetuity" in pretty large print. 
It\'s no secret to the decision makers on the
prospective member state that their decision is
irrevocable.  

The only worlds that have a chance of leaving the
Imperium are those in border areas that have the
support of another major power (like Efate/Regina/
Spinward Marches).  The small nation problem of the
mid-twentieth century is written very large indeed in
the Far Future, when the large nations are composed of
thousands of worlds and the small ones of only
handfuls.

- --Glenn

