    'body' => 'On Tue, 09 Nov 1999 19:41:30 -0700
cos 90 <cos90@powersurfr.com> wrote:

>All this talk about corporations and the various races in
>and around the 3I get me to wondering: what kind of cultural
>expressionism (ie, "the arts") will we find from the various
>races? What do Vilani paintings look like? (Do they even paint
>paintings?) What kind of music do Zhodani listen to? Are the
>arts in the Solomani Confederacy the state-supporting propaganda
>one found in the Eastern Bloc pre-1990 or in Nazi Germany?

I was having similar thoughts myself. In a couple of weeks time,
we\'re taking our kids to Disneyland (tm) for a holiday, and I
was wondering; what do citizens of the 3I do for a holiday?
Do they go to theme parks? Is there a Disney - World - orbiting
some star in the 3I? What has the entertainment industry become?

Here on Terra we have huge tracts of land devoted to tourism.
Even some countries use tourism as their major source of income.
But if you look through the Marches sourcebook there is no indication
that tourism is an important industry anywhere, and there isn\'t even
any mention of things that would be points of interest to a tourist.
So where are all the sight-seeing opportunities & pleasure planets
(like Star Trek\'s Risa)? Where do the luxury liners and safari ships go?

It strikes me that there is very little that would attract tourists to the
Marches.
There\'s the museum at Regina, but that is solitary entertainment and it\'s appeal
could hardly be described as being "fun". Apart from that, there is nothing
that I would consider a "draw" for tourists.

Sheesh. Don\'t the Villani know how to have fun?

Well, maybe I\'m being a bit harsh on them. Other sectors of the Imperium
certainly have things to see, like the cities on Core/Capital, the ringworld
and that star system that orbits in a Kempler(?) rosette. But the Spinward
Marches is strangely bereft of, hmmm, how shall I put this - whimsy.


OK, lets turn this into something practical. I\'d like to ask the TML this
question:
If you lived in the Marches and were planning a vacation with money and time
no object what would you want to go and see?

Graeme
