OTOH, once a culture has a precedent for an annual ceremony to remember
those who have fallen in that culture\'s interests, the ceremonies will
tend to grow to include those who, in peacetime, either fought or served
in that culture\'s interests.  Certainly the Veterans\' Day commemorated
in the United States had its origins in Armistice Day; that doesn\'t mean
that those of us who served in later conflicts are slighted.  Indeed,
those American soldiers who happened to serve in peacetime are
considered just as worthy of honor on Veterans\' Day as those of us who
spent time in combat zones.

Since the 3I has, as antecedents, at least one culture (the Terran
Confederation) that set aside special dates to honor those who fought in
defense of their societies, I would not be surprised to see an
equivalent to Veterans\' Day in the 3I, even though there has been no war
in recent memory that caused casualties of a proportion similar to those
suffered in Terra\'s First World War.

