    'body' => 'Mark Urbin wrote:


>Back in the GDW-Beta list days, Mitch "Ted7" Schwartz designed a racing
>yacht using solar sails.

>I remember linking him up with some nice people from BITS about his
writeup.

>Did this get published by BITS?  If not, are there plans to do so?


I guess this would be me.

It\'s long been my thought that a nice Traveller supplement would be some
kind of \'game\' based on this kind of idea (a bit like TCS or something).  A
kind of Whitbread (the round the world yachting race) in space.

I can envisage there being a solar system with interesting navigation
features that would host a renowned race every, say, ten years that potty
[1] racers come from all over to take part in.  Remember it would take
place over a long period (the yachts taking a while to accelerate!  [2]) -
just like the Whitbread takes the best part of a year to complete.  I\'ve
also envisaged it being a thing that nobles are really into due the
prestige and megacorps due to expense.

Basically, my idea was to have a variety of solar sailing yachts (or rules
for craft construction to meet the races\' specification or \'Rule\') that
would then be used for the race.  [3]  There would be rules for the race so
that the craft and the sailor\'s skills would influence the outcome and the
whole thing could be played in 2 or 3 hours - maybe on some form of sylized
solar system map board.

The snag is that real life has intervened and I\'ve not spent any time
developing this beyond the conceptual stage.  I\'ve also, as you might have
gathered, been concentrating on the Traveller Bibliography.  To tell the
truth, I don\'t think I\'m a gearhead enough to design the craft (that goes
doubly for designing craft design rules) and I\'m insufficiently
knowledgeable about astronomical science to come up with the racing
environment that would prove interesting to design a race around.

I\'d still love to see this happen though and would be delighted if anyone
with the time, inclination and abilities wanted to take these ideas and run
with them.  I reckon it could be a lovely addition to the Traveller milieux
(and would be suitable for any era - except, perhaps, TNE where I struggle
to envisage the time/money/leisure to take part in this [4]).
Any takers?  [5]

tc



[1]  They\'d need to be pretty potty - I assume that solar yachts will be
pretty small - say just two crew - and they\'d be cooped up together for
some time.  Alternatively, they could be bigger vessels with Whitbread 60
type crews (20ish???) who all have a variety of specific duties handling
\'lines\' and such.  I\'d guess quarters would still be *very* cramped to keep
the craft\'s mass down.

[2]  Though of course, nothing would prevent them all starting at speed
which is just how real yachts race.  Half the fun then is hitting the start
line as the signal for the race start goes off.  Not too early, not too
late.

[3] Alternatively, the race could be a \'one design\' type event where all
the craft are identical and it is up the crews to make the difference based
on conditions.

[4] Though perhaps TNErs could be racing for different reasons - none
spring to mind off hand, but I\'m sure someone out there will come up with
something.

[5] If there are TMLers who\'d be interested and do the *real* work but
