    'topic' => 'Those unreliable grav vehicles',
    'index' => 'ee025',
    'month' => '11',
    'body' => 'After doing some research, it seems apparent that you can end up with quite 
a few grav vehicles being disabled without ever being hit by the enemy:

Given the poor HT (8-9) and short maintenance intervals of heavy
grav vehicles, in actual war many are likely to suffer breakdowns,
as vehicles are kept in the field far longer than is safe. Ironically, very 
heavy vehicles are more likely to be pushed too far than their more robust 
bretheren.

(I also assume that an average military mechanic has skill 12-14,
which isn\'t unreasonable -- unless your head mechanic is Scottish,
you can\'t afford to miss more than one or two trips to the garage).

Here are some relevant numbers (using the vehicles from Star Mercs):

                                  Main.
Vehicle                  HT        Interval
TL 9,
Utility Grav Sled        12        82 hours

TL 10,
Light Grav Tank           9        10 hours
Medium Grav Tank          8         7 hours
Heavy Grav Tank           8         5.5 hours
Grav APC                 12        21.5 hours
Air/Space Defense        10         7.2 hours

TL 12,
Astrin APC                8        20.5 hours
Meson Sled               12         7.6 hours
Intrepid Tank             8         5 hours

See Vehicles, 2/e or Compendium II for maintenance rules.

(After looking over the stats for the meson sled and Intrepid grav
tank, it makes me wonder if "real" combat grav vehicles would be
more like the sled -- faster and stealthier*, rather than the
plodding dinosaur of the heavy grav tank).

* -- radical emission cloaking covers radical sound supression
(actually  ), so this extraneous feature should be deleted on the
meson sled.

A generous and sadistic GM,

Brandon Cope

