There *is* one major "disadvantage" to using spetsdods. It\'s
essentially *impossible* to claim that you shot someone
unintentionally. On the other hand, as long as you are using "stun"
loads, nobody is going to get too upset. Spasm[1] loads are going to get
folks *really* upset. Though not as upset as lethal loads.

[1] for those of you who haven\'t read the series, they cause a
virtually instant "lock" of all voluntary muscles. It won\'t kill you,
but it hurts like hell and you need medical care until the effects wear
off (it\'s a sort of viral effect). It takes about 6 *months* to wear
off. 

This makes it an *ideal* military weapon, in that it ties up a maximal
amount of enemy resources in caring for the victim. Yet it\'s not even
lethal, so you can play things down if you accidentally shoot a few
"innocent bystanders".

