    'body' => 'In mail you write:

> Another "peaceful resistance" idea for Traveller:
> Have environment-friendly demonstrants camping on and around the PCs
> spaceship, preventing takeoff and "saving the atmosphere and birds." The
> demonstrants are dressed in bright, cheerful clothes, wear flowers in
> their hair, and all that kind of stuff. A few of them have pet animals
> and birds with them.
>
> Have a flower, man!  ;-)

There are *two* ways this won\'t work.

1. The ship uses a reaction drive. In this case, it\'s kinda hard to
   prove that protesters were there, since anything less than a crowd
   *hundreds* of yards across will be totally vaporized when the
   engines reach full thrust.

2. The ship has thruster plates and/or CG. In which case the ship\'s
   crew merely has to get the protesters off the hull (easily done in
   any of a number of ways. Then take off *slowly* for the first
   thousand feet or so.

Heck, in case 2, you can take off *with* protesters on the hull. Just
hover about 20 feet up, then send a work crew out in suits, and remove
the protesters, one at a time, tie them to a length of rope and lower
them until their friends can catch them. Then drop the rope before the
friends can try to climb up. If they are well secured to the hull, and
fighting, just go up to where the air is thin enough that they pass
out, then remove them, tie them up and drop back down to where you can
lower them by rope. 

Absolute worst case is if they\'ve got oxytanks. That still won\'t let
them last more than an hour or so at 10 km altitude.

And the best part of it is that you\'ve just *shown* them to be idiots
by being *able* to take off without hurting them. 

