    'body' => 'In mail you write:

>> ObTrav: How the ####### do you stop a grav tank this way? I figure it
>> could be done with a small grav car, but wouldn\'t it be possible to
>> drive the tank slowly into contact with the car and then slowly move
>> forward (pushing the car in front of the tank). The tank has a
>> significantly stronger drive, after all.

> You chain your legs (long chain) to a fixed spot on the floor, 
> jump on the marching grav tank from a grav vehicle, and chain your 
> arms to the tank... <grin>
> Carlos Alos-Ferrer

And since this isn\'t a combat situation, a couple of the infantry (in
Battle Dress?) supporting the tanks cut the chain. 

I\'d cut the floor end first, near the protestor\'s feet. hold him up by
that bit of chain while my buddy cuts the chains on the tank. A couple
of quick welds and you\'ve got the guy chained up in his own chains!
Toss him in the paddy wagon and continue.

Personally, I am fond of "riot foam". You generate what amounts to a
8-10 foot deep layer of "soapsuds" (except less toxic!). You can\'t hear
a person standing next to you. You can\'t see your hand in front of your
face. but it doesn\'t interfere with breathing.

Instant isolation means that you no longer *have* a mob. You\'ve
got a few thousand individuals.

Enclose the crowd in the stuff, and as they wander out, or as you
carefully dissolve it around the edges, you grab *individuals*, and
haul them off. 

It\'s hard to call the stuff "cruel" since one of the biggest problems
at demos of the stuff was keeping the local kids from *playing* in it.
They thought it made for the *neatest* game of hide and seek...

Other possibilities that have existed since the late 60s are "liquid
banana peel", and a couple of gases that slowly and gradually render
you incapable of moving. Slowly enough that you\'ve got time to sit
down, and then lie down. If you don\'t you *fall* down. 

Frankly, if these were better known, I\'d expect dictatorships to
*prefer* them. Not only do they avoid those messes with bad publicity,
but they avoid property damage, and allow fewer people to deal with the
protest. And you are pretty much assured of being able to pick up *all*
the protestors. 

