    'body' => 'From: shadow@ (Leonard Erickson)

<Bits snipped>

<Leonard >
That last is the killer in Traveller. That means that you *can\'t* go
even *one* jump away for your vacation, because even with 2 weeks
vacation, it\'d use up your entire vacation just getting there and back!

The only offworld tourists will be rich, retired, or at the very least,
folks with enough seniority to get 4 week vacations. And even the
latter aren\'t going to go more than a jump away. 
</Leonard>

<Me>
Assuming of course that people get only two weeks.  The norm in this country (and NZ too ?) is four weeks annual leave.  As a result, a couple of years ago, we had the lowest absenteeism in the industrialised world.  Then they cut the public holidays down and absenteeism went up.

<Leonard>
Glorified amusement parks, like Disney World, are going to be *local*.
Besides, given the *vast* cultural differences between worlds,
attracting folks from offworld isn\'t all that likely anyway.

And later .....

This is an apparently often overlooked point. In Traveller the average
person *never* leaves their home system, and may never leave their home
planet. The exceptions being *mostly* folks who enlist in the Imperial
forces or who have a job that sends them offworld. 
</Leonard>

Would that then not be a *good* reason for people to be leaving a world ?  There are hundreds (if not thousands) of worlds in the TU with <500K population.  The people on these worlds won\'t have a lot to do in their spare time.  Ergo, they work longer hours \'cos there\'s not a lot to do in their spare time.  Ergo, you give them longer leave as compensation.

You\'ve also got added pressure from bored juveniles and restless people (ie : Travellers) wanting to do *something* other than watch groats graze.  What is there for a teenager to do on a world with GTL 12 and population of 5000 souls ?  Not a great deal.  What do they do in response ?  Hop on a passing starship and see a bit of the galaxy.

The average Joe (sorry, Eneri) may well see another culture/world and his/her/its\'/their own as being quite exotic.  They would particularly notice the differences.  This would then be an added attraction in visiting offworld.

I suspect travel offworld would be not be limited to the rich and the Forces.  People may only do it every few years or once in their lifetime, but it\'s probably only uncommon at worst.

What is there to do another world ?  BUCKETLOADS !!!!  Travel to a different part of your own country and have a look around; you\'ll quickly find things of interest.  Tourism isn\'t just flashing lights and dancing, it\'s about seeing and experiencing stuff that you can\'t do at home.  Just being \'somewhere else\' is often a thrill in and of itself.  There\'d be HEAPS to do in the Marches.  I can think of at least two subsectors that\'d make great pubcrawls ........

Dave
