To leave, the country that wants to leave has to decide (by whatever means
that country uses). I\'m not aware of any mechanism that prevents this.

To enter, the country has to decide to join and all the current members
have to agree.

Each of these decisions is made by the counties head of state,
although the laws of a given country might require a referendum
or new laws to be passed or acts of parliment or whatever.
