    'index' => 'ee109',
    'month' => '11',
    'body' => 'Jed Docherty wrote:
> How do you say Efate?  Boughene? Pscias?  Is there a guide to the
> pronounciation of system names?

I always judge that there are many ways to say a single name, due to
dialect differences and such. Also, lots local names for the same system
might be in use, due to different languages, cultural reasons et al.

For examples of local name variations, study how many of the European
countries are named in each others\' languages. Germany, Tyskland, and
Deutchland are all different names for the same place (in English,
Swedish, and German, respectively).

Also, study how different the name "England" is pronounced by an
Englishman, a NYC American, and a Texas American.

Another source of different names is from cultural reasons. For example,
China is referred to as the "Middle Kingdom" in Mandarin (Chinese). In
Traveller, all the inhabitants on a world might call it Home.

/Jens \'Spacejens\' Rydholm
