> 
> That\'s easy. I\'d hop the first megaliner to somewhere else!  The Marches are
> Yonkers as portrayed in Hello Dolly or Montana in an old western. People go
> there to work, to build a home, to hide from people they don\'t want to find
> them "back east". Nobody goes there to vacation.

Interstellar travel is expensive and (more importantly) time-consuming
enough that nobody other than the very very *very* rich will vacation more
than a few parsecs from home, and the vast majority will stay in their
home systems.  Any system with a reasonably large population (and a
healthy economy) will have a multitude of resorts, parks, and so forth
available.  Consider that middle passage through one jump round trip for a
family of four is Cr 64k, and two weeks of the precious vacation time
blown in transit. 

