_101 Ballistic Flightless Birds_, actually, which will feature thrown
penguins along with catapulted ostriches, dropped emus, hurled dodos, and
so forth.

> Along with a list of books and magazines (okay tc!) and some Patrons. 

Patron 102:

A nervous-looking man approaches the party in a quiet section of the
starport.  He is leading a 70cm tall penguin on a thin leash.  After
glancing around to be sure he\'s not overheard, he offers the party Cr 100
to throw the penguin.  Before anyone has time to answer, his eyes widen in
panic; he hands the leash to one of the party (dropping it if they refuse
to take it) and departs at a run.  The penguin stands calmly. 

1. Everything is as it seems.  If and when someone in the party throws
   the penguin at least two meters, the man will emerge from hiding,
   where he has been keeping the party under surveillance, and hand
   over Cr 100.  If the party appears to be leaving the immediate
   area, the man will confront the party and demand his penguin back.

2. The man is never seen again, no matter how many times and how
   hard the penguin is thrown.  It is a difficult task (dexterity
   and thrown weapon skill) to avoid injuring the penguin on the
   second and subsequent tosses.

3. The man is (more) psychotic (than the apparent situation indicates).
   If the penguin is thrown, he will attack the party with a machete,
   screaming "My baby!  My baby!".

4. The man is actually an agent for PETA, trying to dupe the party
   into revealing their barbarous anti-animal prejudices.  If the
