>> --
>>
>I beleave that ST:TMP was to be the new ST tv show. Thats why you have all
>of the long shots and character walk-ins. But well in pre-poduction Star
>Wars came out, made a ton of money (much more than a tv show could ever
>make). Paramount saw what SW was doing, and knowing with all the trekkies
>out there, it had a hit movie know matter how bad it was. So the pilot
>(ST:TMP) was turned into a movie and scripting for the next movie (ST: TWoK)
>begain.
>

According to Shatner\'s book (Movie Memories):

Paramount was planning a ST tv show (ST Phase II) as the flagship show for the
launch of a Paramount TV network (which is what they eventually did with
Voyager). They pulled from the idea of the TV show and (according to rumour,
when Eisner saw how close encounters was doing) converted to the idea of the
movie. But the script for the TV pilot served as the first draft of the movie
script, and is much the same, apart from the different ending.

The story about WoK is unlikely, since a) the first film had a considerably
higher budget than the second, and b) in Shatner\'s book he has verbatim
interviews with the scriptwriters, the director, Nimoy, Kelley and Montalban
and it\'s pretty clear from all of them that the idea for a Space Seed sequel
came after ST:TMP.

And by the way, I like TMP the best out of all of them, barring First Contact.

