    'body' => 'Dear Folks -

Leonard said:
>BTW, it occurs to me that writing up a few "survival race" courses from
>the 3I might make a good "non-combat" scenario to get players used to
>working as a team. There are some interesting possibilities if you pick
>the right sort of planet.

You may be interested to know that I ran the survival race from "Lee\'s Guide To
Interstellar Adventure" on Tavonni, when Caradoc was first scouting out the
planet.

I wrote up about 20 NPC\'s, including Baroness Heidi\'s younger brother and even
an undercover Zho. An obscure mob called "Unifoods" (they may actually have been
in the original adventure?) ran the thing, with the Caradoc PC\'s becoming
entangled halfway through.

Turned out that the Zho was using the event as part of his cover, while
performing a deep recon prior to the 5FW. He initially escaped the characters in
a Zho Leader Scout ship that had been hidden on the surface, only to have them
pursue and board it in orbit. He threw out some lifepods and went EVA, attached
himself to the PC\'s ship and deployed one of those foam drop capsules. When the
PC\'s shot up and/or captured the rest of the crew, they thought they had
finished. They re-entered Tavonni\'s atmosphere, at which point the Zho abandoned
(their) ship and re-entered independantly.

He survived to become a Zho squadron commander in the 5FV.

(Don\'t you just love playing NPC\'s that are as pesky as the players themselves?
;-)
