Nope. ST:TMP was originally what was supposed to be the pilot of a second
Star Trek series, one that would have had Decker as the first officer,
Ilia as the navigator, and Xon as science officer, with the occasional
guest appearance by Leonard Nimoy as Spock, retired from Star Fleet and
teaching on Vulcan.

Then Star Wars comes out and makes big bucks at the box office, so Paramount
decides to scrap the TV series (which was iffy to begin with) and do a 
feature film. Since everyone was crowing about the great special effects in
Star Wars, the powers-that-be at Paramount put in lots of special effects
shots; when the film came in overlong, they cut scenes of dialog instead
of effects shots.

The end result was a snore. And when Paramount heard what Gene wanted to 
do for the *second* ST film (Kirk & co. go back in time to prevent JFK\'s
assassination -- Spock becomes the hidden figure on the grassy knoll...),
TPTB @ Paramount give Gene an office and a title ("Creative Consultant")
and proceed to ignore him totally from there on in...


