Well, in my referee\'s TU, ships can exit jumpspace closer than 100
diameters from a major celestial body, if the astrogator, pilot, and
engineer all roll successfully (difficulty is based on intended distance
of jump exit from the body in question).  The nearest jump I\'ve seen in
our campaign has been 10 diameters from a planet (we were dropping a
battalion of jump troops), which required (IIRC) Formidable [3D] rolls. 
My character (the commander of the regiment to which the jump troops
were assigned) would not have allowed the risk of jumping closer than 10
diameters (had the issue been suggested by the Navy), due to the
increased risks to all ships in the jump.  He would rather have given up
a portion of tactical surprise, than risk a ship with some of _his_
soldiers catastrophically misjumping.

Of course, YPMV (your parsecage may vary)....

