    'body' => 'Tim MacPherson <timac@home.com> wrote

>Can anyone recommend a novel that is "traveller-like" in atmosphere?

Folks have pretty much covered the old stuff, though I would also add in
Andre Norton\'s SF. 

Her Solar Queen and other free trader books especially: Sargasso of Space,
Plague Ship, & Postmarked the Stars are all good choices. 

For more modern books I highly recommend both the Hellflower trilogy by
Eluki bes Shahar: Hellflower, Dark Traders, & Archangel Blues

& the Exordium series by Sherwood Smith & Dave Trowbridge:  The Phoenix in
Flight, The Ruler of Naught, A Prison Unsought, Rifter\'s Covenant, & The
Throne of Kronos

Both series have a *very* Traveller-like feel, but are also clearly 90s
SF, so there are an excellent guide for how to update Traveller while
still preserving its distinctive feel. 


