> >attempt, (say, drives a truck at high speed through a crowded pedestrian
> >mall,) does the peace officer get blamed? Or does he just get blamed if
> >the chase was not successful in catching the criminal?

It will depend on the circumstances of the chase and the crime that the bad 
guy committed.
But generally if the officer followed departmental guidelines then there 
would not be any criminal action.  Of course civilly it is another 
matter.  As an example an criminal who has committed a violent felony would 
be pursued while a misdemeanor or a traffic offence we would break off.

