passenger jet, I\'ve been higher than the summit of Mt. Everest, yet I\'m
fascinated by the people who climb it.  There was a bit in an old Niven
story "Elephant", were Beowulf Shaffer was visiting Earth, and saw people
racing old autos on a stretch of freeway.  His reaction when he realized
that the cars had neither radar nor autopilot..

Earlier this year the lead story on the news was that two guys in a baloon
had manged to fly around the world.  Hardly cutting edge tech, but it was
the struggle to do it with what is "primative" tech that made it interesting.

The same will hold true for our theoretical solar/mag sail racers.. The
promoters of the race circut will emphasis the hands-on nature of the
event, with on-board cameras showing racers making furious scribbled
calculations and shooting azmuths.
