Over the years I\'ve found the best solution for Traveller  is  to
have the party  still  *in  service*.  In  my  current  Traveller
campaign the group started out as the crew of a IN Gazelle  class
Close Escort in the Regina subsector in 1105.  They are now an IN
troubleshooter team (aka "Irregular Ops") assigned to one of  the
fleets in the 5FW (rimward of the Sword Worlds) ... and now 1  PC
is an ImpMarine NCO.  Not  only  does  this  give  the  party  an
\'excuse\' to be together, they are  also  much  more  disciplined.
Also, if they get hold of any equipment which could unbalance the
game they have to hand  it  in.  Adventures  include:  smuggling,
intelligence gathering, counter-terrorist, search and rescue  (of
lifeboats after fleet engagements),  damage  control  on  capital
ships, a murder mystery, they\'ve also been POWs and diplomats.

Regards PLST
