The first adventure I ran (1974), started in a town where the party
was hired as bodyguards for a pair of merchants.  They traveled down
a river having adventures with lizard men and a troll on a bridge.
Then it was through an enchanted forest and a run in with elves
over chopping down a sacred tree that was settled peacefully.  Out
of the forest the party entered a town where the merchants did their
business while the PC\'s found rooms in the inn.  An "encounter"
between a PC and the innkeeper\'s daughter lead to a rapid exit from
the town the next morning...Julio was always something of a cad.
The party traveled into the hill country toward the mountains
meeting some hobbits (friendly) and a pair of wandering giants
(tried to steal the horses) along the way.  Later they came upon a
wizard working some sort of weather magic at the edge of a cliff,
and one of the party "discovered" she had magical abilities.  A
tribe of goblins provided a big combat along a mountain path.  Once
over the mountains they delivered the merchants through the "bad
lands" patrolled by tribes of horsemen into the "Peaceful Kingdom
and the "Celestial City."  This completed their adventure and not
wanting to continue with those characters the players and I ended
the campaign.  Not one dungeon crawl in the year long campaign.
Now, in the *second* adventure...<g>

You know, recounting that tail makes me want to run it again.  I
