That\'s true, but that\'s just tradecraft.
I was referring to the statement in question talking about considering how
people are going to _interpret_ it.

I probably should have put more detail, because I would agree that rule-sets
need to consider some possible interpretations, but what I disagree about is
that you should try and design a rule-set that is "munchkin" or
