I think you need to look into the actual "mechanics" involved in rock
dropping. *Nobody* "haul[s] big rocks into orbit". It takes an unreal
amount of power, even by Traveller standards, to shift the orbit of a
"big rock" so that it\'ll hit a planet *months* later. 

If you want something to hit before there\'s time for a courier to leave
and bring back reinforcements, the situation is rather different. You
are talking about "small" rocks (ship sized) and it winds up being
easier to threaten to drop a "junker" ship on them under autopilot. 

You need *enormous* (and expensive!) drives to shift rocks. 

